M|references|Instead of guessing what works, systematically analyze top-performing cnt in your niche and extract proven patterns.
M|references|- The 6-Step Framework (Niche ID, Scrape, Analyze, Playbook, Layer Voice, Convert)
M|references|- The Formula
M|references|- Reverse Engineering Checklist
M|references|Identify 10-20 creators in your space who consistently get high engagement:
M|references|**Selection criteria:**
M|references|- Posting consistently (3+ times/week)
M|references|- High engagement rate relative to follower count
M|references|- Audience overlap with your target market
M|references|- Mix of established and rising creators
M|references|**Where to find them:**
M|references|- LinkedIn: Search by industry keywords, check "People also viewed"
M|references|- Twitter/X: Check who your target audience follows and engages with
M|references|- Use tools like SparkToro, Followerwonk, or manual research
M|references|- Look at who gets featured in industry newsletters
M|references|Gather 500-1000+ posts from your identified creators for analysis:
M|references|**Tools:**
M|references|- **Apify** ÔÇö LinkedIn scraper, Twitter scraper actors
M|references|- **Phantom Buster** ÔÇö Multi-platform automation
M|references|- **Export tools** ÔÇö Platform-specific export features
M|references|- **Manual collection** ÔÇö For smaller datasets, copy/paste into spreadsheet
M|references|**Data to collect:**
M|references|- Post text/cnt
M|references|- Engagement metrics (likes, comments, shares, saves)
M|references|- Post format (text-only, carousel, video, image)
M|references|- Posting time/day
M|references|- Hook/first line
M|references|- CTA used
M|references|- Topic/theme
M|references|Sort and analyze the data to find patterns:
M|references|**Quantitative analysis:**
M|references|- Rank posts by engagement rate
M|references|- Identify top 10% performers
M|references|- Look for format patterns (do carousels outperform?)
M|references|- Check timing patterns (best days/times)
M|references|- Compare topic performance
M|references|**Qualitative analysis:**
M|references|- What hooks do top posts use?
M|references|- How long are high-performing posts?
M|references|- What emotional triggers appear?
M|references|- What formats repeat?
M|references|- What topics consistently perform?
M|references|**Questions to answer:**
M|references|- What's the average length of top posts?
M|references|- Which hook types appear most in top 10%?
M|references|- What CTAs drive most comments?
M|references|- What topics get saved/shared most?
M|references|doc repeatable patterns you can use:
M|references|**Hook patterns to codify:**
M|references|```
M|references|Pattern: "I [unexpected action] and [surprising result]"
M|references|Example: "I stopped posting daily and my engagement doubled"
M|references|Why it works: Curiosity gap + contrarian
M|references|Pattern: "[Specific number] [things] that [outcome]:"
M|references|Example: "7 pricing mistakes that cost me $50K:"
M|references|Why it works: Specificity + loss aversion
M|references|Pattern: "[Controversial take]"
M|references|Example: "Cold outreach is dead."
M|references|Why it works: Pattern interrupt + invites debate
M|references|```
M|references|**Format patterns:**
M|references|- Carousel: Hook slide Ôćĺ Problem Ôćĺ Solution steps Ôćĺ CTA
M|references|- Thread: Hook Ôćĺ Promise Ôćĺ Deliver Ôćĺ Recap Ôćĺ CTA
M|references|- Story post: Hook Ôćĺ Setup Ôćĺ Conflict Ôćĺ Resolution Ôćĺ Lesson
M|references|**CTA patterns:**
M|references|- Question: "What would you add?"
M|references|- Agreement: "Agree or disagree?"
M|references|- Share: "Tag someone who needs this"
M|references|- Save: "Save this for later"
M|references|Take proven patterns and make them yours with these voice principles:
M|references|**"Smart friend who figured something out"**
M|references|- Write like you're texting advice to a friend
M|references|- Share discoveries, not lectures
M|references|- Use "I found that..." not "You should..."
M|references|- Be helpful, not preachy
M|references|**Specific > Vague**
M|references|```
M|references|ÔŁî "I made good revenue"
M|references|Ôťů "I made $47,329"
M|references|ÔŁî "It took a while"
M|references|Ôťů "It took 47 days"
M|references|ÔŁî "A lot of people"
M|references|Ôťů "2,847 people"
M|references|```
M|references|**Short. Breathe. Land.**
M|references|- One idea per sentence
M|references|- Use line breaks liberally
M|references|- Let important points stand alone
M|references|- Create rhythm: short, short, longer explanation
M|references|```
M|references|ÔŁî "I spent three years building my business the wrong way before I finally realized that the key to success was focusing on fewer things and doing them exceptionally well."
M|references|Ôťů "I built wrong for 3 years.
M|references|Then I figured it out.
M|references|Focus on less.
M|references|Do it exceptionally well.
M|references|Everything changed."
M|references|```
M|references|**Write from emotion**
M|references|- Start with how you felt, not what you did
M|references|- Use emotional words: frustrated, excited, terrified, obsessed
M|references|- Show vulnerability when authentic
M|references|- Connect the feeling to the lesson
M|references|```
M|references|ÔŁî "Here's what I learned about pricing"
M|references|Ôťů "I was terrified to raise my prices.
M|references|My hands were shaking when I sent the email.
M|references|Here's what happened..."
M|references|```
M|references|Bridge from engagement to business results:
M|references|**Soft conversions:**
M|references|- nl signups in bio/comments
M|references|- Free resource offers in follow-up comments
M|references|- DM triggers ("Comment X and I'll send you...")
M|references|- Profile visits Ôćĺ optimized profile with clear CTA
M|references|**Direct conversions:**
M|references|- Link in comments (not post body on LinkedIn)
M|references|- Contextual product mentions within valuable cnt
M|references|- Case study posts that naturally showcase your work
M|references|- "If you want help with this, DM me" (sparingly)
M|references|```
M|references|1. Find what's already working (don't guess)
M|references|2. Extract the patterns (hooks, formats, CTAs)
M|references|3. Layer your authentic voice on top
M|references|4. Test and iterate based on your own data
M|references|```
